        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The valley of Tyropeum lay between the temple on the eastern hill and Solomon's palace, which was on the western side of it. The name of this wife was probably Psusennes, last of the twenty-first dynasty. 2 Chronicles 8:11",
